width=device-width : it sets the width of the page to follow the screen-width of the device 

initial-scale=1 : it sets the initial zoom level when the page is first loaded by the browser

.container : class provides a responsive fixed width container

.container-fluid: class provides a full width container

Grids:
------

xs (for phones)
sm (for tablets)
md (for desktops)
lg (for larger desktops)

<div class="row"> : creation of row

<div class="col-sm-4">.col-sm-4</div>: creation of columns

<small> : element is used to create a lighter, secondary text in any heading

<mark>highlight</mark> : highlights the text between these tags.

<abbr> :The abbr element is used to mark up an abbreviation or acronym

<blockquote>  : The blockquote element is used to present content from another source.

 .blockquote-reverse : To show the quote on the right 

<dl>  : The dl element indicates a description list

<dt>  :

<dd> :

<code> :Inline snippets of code should be embedded in the code element

<kbd>  :To indicate input that is typically entered via the keyboard.

<pre>  :For multiple lines of code

.text-muted,.text-primary,.text-success,.text-info,.text-warning,.text-danger: for text colors

.bg-primary,.bg-success,bg-info,bg-warning,.bg-danger :  for background colors

classes:
----------

.lead	: Makes a paragraph stand out 

.small	: Indicates smaller text (set to 85% of the size of the parent)

.text-left	Indicates left-aligned text	

.text-center	Indicates center-aligned text
	
.text-right	Indicates right-aligned text	

.text-justify	Indicates justified text
	
.text-nowrap	Indicates no wrap text	

.text-lowercase	: Indicates lowercased text
	
.text-uppercase	: Indicates uppercased text
	
.text-capitalize   :	Indicates capitalized text
	
.initialism	: Displays the text inside an <abbr> element in a slightly smaller font size

.list-unstyled : Removes the default list-style and left margin on list items (works on both <ul> and <ol>). This class only applies to immediate children list items (to remove the default list-style from any nested lists, apply this class to any nested lists as well)	

.list-inline	Places all list items on a single line.

.dl-horizontal	: Lines up the terms (<dt>) and descriptions (<dd>) in <dl> elements side-by-side. Starts off like default <dl>s, but when  the browser window expands, it will line up side-by-side.

.pre-scrollable	: Makes a <pre> element scrollable	

.table-striped : class adds zebra-stripes to a table

.table-bordered  : class adds borders to a table

.table-hover : class enables a hover state on table rows

.table-condensed : class makes a table more compact by cutting cell padding in half

.active	         Applies the hover color to the table row or table cell

.success	Indicates a successful or positive action

.info	        Indicates a neutral informative change or action

.warning	Indicates a warning that might need attention

.danger	        Indicates a dangerous or potentially negative action

.table-responsive  : class creates a responsive table which will scroll horizontally on small devices (under 768px)

Bootstrap Image Shapes :
========================

.img-rounded : class adds rounded corners to an image (not available in IE8)

.img-circle  : class shapes the image to a circle 

.img-thumbnail : class shapes the image to a thumbnail

.embed-responsive-item : for creating responsive videos

.well     : class adds a rounded border around an element with a gray background color and some padding





